<br>
Example. Prior to Kunark there were two dragons to kill and way too many people to kill them. Because Verant had to keep the high-end drops rare, they put the dragons on week long timers. We all remember what a fuckstain that was.<br>
<br>
Then came Kunark with more content, but the high-end mobs were still kept on week-long timers. However, more and more guilds became capable of killing these mobs. The situtation really didn't get any better once people started reaching 60.<br>
<br>
Finally there is Velious and the situtation Emarr is in now. Even MORE content including an endgame dungeon (which by the way is quite contested). But has anything really changed except for the fact that there is more shit to kill? You are still waiting in lines to kill mobs you have killed a zillion times over because of spawn timers. And the spawn timers are there to keep the items rare so you keep playing. Nothing's really changed. It's still EverCamp.<br>
<br>
